@startuml fig-S07-e2-message-flow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title S07 — E2 Path: Local Hit, Forwarded Query and Cache Hit

participant "tester" as C #FFE0B2
participant "dns_resolver\n:5300/UDP" as R #C8E6C9
participant "upstream_dns\n:53/UDP" as U #E3F2FD

== LOCAL ZONE HIT ==
C -> R : Query A: host1.lab.local (ID=0x01)
note right of R : Found in local zone
R -[#43A047]-> C : Response: 10.0.0.1 (NOERROR)

== FORWARDED QUERY ==
C -> R : Query A: example.com (ID=0x02)
note right of R : Not in zone, not in cache
R -> U : Forward query A: example.com (ID=0x02)
U -[#43A047]-> R : Response: 93.184.216.34 (TTL=300)
R -[#43A047]-> C : Response: 93.184.216.34

note right of R : Cached with TTL=300s

== CACHE HIT ==
C -> R : Query A: example.com (ID=0x03)
note right of R #C8E6C9 : Served from cache\n(no upstream query)
R -[#43A047]-> C : Response: 93.184.216.34

note over U : No packet sent\nto upstream

legend right
  Three scenarios demonstrable in PCAP:
  1. Local zone answer (no upstream)
  2. Forwarded to upstream (two UDP pairs)
  3. Cache hit (single UDP pair, no upstream)
  Validates R1–R5 in S07.json
endlegend
@enduml
